HEADWORD: Symphysis
<hw>Sym"phy*sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Symphyses</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <?/, fr. <?/
to make to grow together; <grk>sy`n</grk> with + <?/ to cause to grow;
to grow.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>An articulation
formed by intervening cartilage; <as>as, the pubic
<ex>symphysis</ex></as>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The union or
coalescence of bones; also, the place of union or coalescence; <as>as,
the <ex>symphysis</ex> of the lower jaw</as>. Cf.
<er>Articulation</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
